snippet.title: Feuille Morte: Relaxing Ambient Sci Fi Music for Autumn
snippet.description:
Hey everyone!

A little life update: A week and a half ago I broke my arm. It has been a rough time especially since I've never broken a bone before, so everything is new to me. All in all, I'm grateful and have been resting and recovering. It could have been much worse. Even while in recovery, I'm so excited for Futurescapes and moving into the fall season. So I wanted to still make something for you all! Feuille Morte (meaning Dead Leaf) is a simple video that I made while having only one working arm haha I can't work at my regular speed and I don't know how long it will be before I'm back to normal but I'm excited to share more videos and music with you this season! Happy fall and stay safe!

snippet.title: The Whispering Woods: Emotional Ambient Adventure Fantasy Music (Inspired by Video Game Music)
snippet.description:
Ari leapt to the fallen tree before him as the glow of dawn broke through the Whispering Wood's violet canopy. Voices from deep within the forest called forth a desperate invitation as he mustered the courage to move on. Though a harrowing journey lay ahead, he knew the heart of this dangerous woodland kept hidden the answers to saving his dying home.
___________________________

As many of you know, my full time work is composing music for video games. This video is the first of what I have wanted to include on Futurescapes since I started the channel. As a video game composer, I write in many different styles, genres and emotions beyond that of classic space and science fiction. One of my favourites is that of story driven adventure games often found in the indie scene. Games like the Ori series, Journey, RiME, Gris and so much more. I hope you enjoy this glimpse into other aspects of my composing! Many more to come!

snippet.title: Voyager: Ambient SPACE Music for Colonizing the Cosmos (Relaxing Sci Fi Music)
snippet.description:
They call us The Great Heroes. Space faring colonizers sent to expand the diplomatic reach of our honourable Earth among the stars. Ever since I was a child I idolized The Great Heroes that went before us. Like superstars they would board the ship of their launch year with the rest of their crew, waving to an overjoyed barrage of cameras and reportermen. I never thought I would get the chance to follow in their footsteps, yet here I am. I said farewell to my crewmates just three suns ago. Five members, sent to pave the way for future colonization on five of the most habitable planets in the galaxy. If my efforts prove fruitful (and the planet survivable), I may receive colony members within three to five Earth years. Until then I build, forage and research. Doing everything in my power to establish a veritable home for our kind. This is my duty, my calling. For I, am A Voyager.

snippet.title: Rift: Ambient SPACE Music for Traversing Celestial Phenomena (Relaxing Sci Fi Music)
snippet.description:
Log 237: It is currently Earth day 104 of our journey. As we approach the mouth of The Rift, scientific phenomena have increased exponentially within the ship's hull. The fabric of space appears to be physically fluctuating at astronomical rates, causing structural damage to the ship's interior walls as they buckle under immense pressure from the outside. Crew members have begun experiencing hallucinatory events of unexplainable intensity. It is unclear as to whether these events are forgeries of the mind, visions of what lies beyond The Rift, or attempts of communication from an unknown source. Log recordings will continue as I or the crew are alive and able. We pray that entry into The Rift will reveal to us answers that benefit the future of mankind. This concludes the entry of log 237.

This video is inspired by the Fallout game series in light of the awesome new Prime series! The Fallout series (specifically Fallout 3) has been at the top of my favourites list since its release. I remember renting it from Blockbuster (lol Blockbuster, good times) and spending the entire weekend playing through the whole game. I was absolutely obsessed with the world that was created (thanks to inspiration from the original 2 games, no doubt). Everything from The Wasterland and post apocalyptic societies to the retro aesthetic and vintage jazz music. This video is intentionally made to capture the essence of Fallout 3 and the way Inon Zur's music compliments with sparse thematic elements that fill the vast emptiness of The Wasteland in an unforgettable sound. Pair that with radioactive wind and old radio music and you've got yourself the essence of the Fallout series.

snippet.title: Contact: Ambient Sci Fi Music for Discovering the Extraterrestrial (Relaxing Sci Fi Music)
snippet.description:
I approached it with the utmost caution, my feet drifting in wisps through the tall withered brush. With each step the gentle whisper of arid blades drew me ever closer to the migrant being. As the tips of my quivering fingers reached nervously to meet its rusted surface, a roar of energy emanated from deep within its metallic core. Lumbering appendages unfurled loosely with the rattle of mechanical components as it awoke, rising up as a beast from slumber to meet my gaze. It lifted from the meadow's covering to unveil its daunting breadth just as a luminous sphere flickered to life on its front plate. It lingered apprehensively, glaring toward my stature as I stood petrified in the now perilous pasture. I knew the next move would be mine to make...

Youtube has not only opened an opportunity for me to have a creative side project that I'm passionate about, it has also allowed me to connect with so many other creative people that share similar passions. These relaxing videos are so fun and rewarding for me to make and I love finding interesting new worlds to create. I've published a bunch of long form videos, shorts, released music and wallpapers on Bandcamp, and as of writing this have just hit 17,000 subscribers!
